Using the link power as determined above, MDS+DS yields a CV score of 0.88, while the lasso is slightly better with a score of 0.7. Changing the link power (for example running the regression to find a power per-LOOCV round) did not significantly effect the score.

Unlike the NPI model, all of the fitted models used a large number of unpenalised functions (the mean EDF being 33).

